post_text:
Be Safe Incident Update

Keeping our students and schools safe is our first priority. Late last night we received a tip on our new Be Safe system that contained concerning information regarding comments made by a student on social media. We immediately alerted local law enforcement and a threat assessment was performed. Through collaboration with local law enforcement last night and early this morning, the situation was addressed without the student being on school property. Students, staff, and the school were not in imminent danger. Again, keeping our students safe is a our top priority and we are thankful for the support and assistance from our students, staff, families, and community.

We understand that these statements often spur questions. However, due to student confidentiality this is the only information available for release.
